**HECS-HELP repayments** are income-contingent: no repayments are required if your taxable income is below **$54,435** (FY2025–26). Above this threshold, repayments range from 1% to 10% of income. With $72,000 income and a $35,000 balance, your annual compulsory repayment is approximately $2,520 — while indexation (CPI-based) adds approximately $1,120 back to the balance.

This calculator uses the **ATO's Schedule 9 repayment thresholds** for FY2025–26 to project your annual repayment, indexation charge, net debt reduction, and years to becoming HECS-free.
